The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Ahmedabad, Feb. 4 (PTI): The body of a seven-year-old girl was found in the toilet of a municipal school, adjacent to where she studied, in Ahmedabad today.           Sangeeta, a student of Class III, had gone missing two days ago. An investigation has been started and authorities of both schools are being questioned.                  
	 Washington (PTI): The US special representative for Pakistan and Afghanistan, Richard Holbrooke, will visit India next week to listen to Delhis point of view on the Afghan-Pak issue and its perspective on Afghanistan, the state department has said. Kashmir will not be discussed, spokesperson Robert Wood said.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): A two-year-old has been raped and later dumped in a gutter in a north-west suburb in Mumbai. The girl and her family were sleeping on a pavement near Vile Parle railway station on Monday night. The girl was rescued by fire officials and was taken to a local hospital.                   
	 New York (PTI): An NRI teenager, reported missing two weeks ago, has returned, saying she had run away because she felt embarrassed at being expelled from university. Erica Desai, 19, rang up an emergency number on Tuesday and told police she had been abducted but later admitted she had run away.                   
	 Bhopal (PTI): A man allegedly stabbed to death two of his daughters, seriously injured two others and his wife before trying to commit suicide in Bhopal on Wednesday. Shafiq Mohammed, 50, had written a note saying he was facing financial hardships and was unable to support his family. Mohammed and his family are also alleged to have taken poison.                  
	 Haridwar (PTI): At least 10 people were injured in an explosion in a furnace at a Bhel plant in Haridwar on Wednesday. Six fire tenders were called to douse the blaze. The injured have been taken to hospital.
                                                                                                                           
